R1: The setting seems to be a living room, so it seems appropriate that the robot was cleaning it. Since there are no people, having food/drinks or talking would not be appropriate.
R2: Since there are people, it does not seem appropriate that the robot would be cleaning the living room. Actions involving interaction seem more appropriate now.
R3: Since the robot appears to be leaving the room, it seems appropriate that it was cleaning the following room. Also, it could be carrying cold food, that was not eaten by the people in the room, or empty plates, to the kitchen.
R4: It appears the robot is going upstairs, so it would seem more appropriate that it was carrying a small object (perhaps even food or drinks). Large objects and cleaning seem inappropriate, since there are people in the house, and music in the room.
R5: It seems the robot is very near a person, so vaccum cleaning seems very inappropriate, as it would disturb the person. Similarly, moping and carrying big objects could also disturb the person, so I seem them as inappropriate, whereas food/drink and small objects seem appropriate.
R6: Since there are many people, a sleeping person and a pet, cleaning or carrying large objects seem rather inappropriate (and vaccum even more, as it could wake up the person). Food/drink could be enjoyed by the people without disturbing the sleeping one.
R7: It seems appropriate that the robot is cleaning, as there is only one person in the room, and the robot seems to be going in his opposite direction. For the same reason (going in the opposite direction) it does not seem appropriate that the robot would be carrying food or drinks, or starting conversation, as there is no one on the robot's direction.
R8: Since there is an awake and a sleeping person, it seems appropriate anything that could be useful but that does not disturb the sleeping one (food, drink or small object). In this case, since the robot is so close to the sleeping person, starting a conversation would also be very inappropriate, as well as carrying big object that would make much noise or vaccum cleaning.
R9: There is only one person in the circle, so carrying drinks/food is alright (I would just not say appropriate as there are more people outside the circle). Cleaning does not seem appropriate, as there a person very close.
R10: There are no people in the circle. Mopping seems appropriate, since no one is there, but  vaccum cleaning is noisy and could disturb people in the room, as well as the dog.
R11: the robot is heading towards the person, so it seems appropriate that it could be bringing him something useful or enjoyable, or talk (and not cleaning or carrying big objects).
R12: In the small circle there are many people, so any cleaning or carrying large objects is not appropriate (especially cleaning, as there is no room to clean). Food/drink seem more appropriate
R13: robot seems to heading towards the child, so it seems very appropriate to carry a toy (and also appropriate to carry food and drinks). Not cleaning, as there are more people in the room.
R14: Same as before (many people), but now there is music, so extra noise seems even more inappropriate.
R15: There is a person in the circle and more people in the room.
R16: There are no people around, so it seems more appropriate to be cleaning (and not to carry drink/food/etc). Noise is not a problem, since the room is empty.
R17: Robot seems to be heading out, so it could be appropriate to carry small objects (or cold food, to remove it from the living room). Noisy actions would be inappropriate since there are still people in the room.
R18: There is a sleeping person, so noisy actions are very inappropriate (talking is not very noisy, and people seem to be doing it, so it is not inappropriate). There are still other people in the room, so it seems appropriate that food/drinks/small objects are carried.
R19: The robot seems to be going in the direction of the group of talking people, so either to bring them food/drinks or to talk, could be appropriate (although they are already talking, so start a conversation could be neutral). There is a sleeping person and a pet, so no noisy actions are appropriate.
R20: There is no one sleeping, but noise can still disturb the several people in the room. There are people in the circle, so it could make sense to carry food/drink/small objects.
